📖 Theory
What is SSH?

SSH (Secure Shell) is a secure protocol used to connect to remote Linux servers.

Example:

Laptop
    │
    │ SSH
    ▼
Ubuntu Server

Default SSH Port:

22
🛠️ Task 1 – Check SSH Status

Ubuntu

sudo systemctl status ssh

Start SSH

sudo systemctl start ssh

Enable at boot

sudo systemctl enable ssh
🛠️ Task 2 – Find Your IP
hostname -I

or

ip addr
